## 9. Training Loop

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| `epochs` | **60** |
| `patience` | **8** (early stopping) |
| [seed](file:///home/raj/Documents/CODING/Hackathon/ANRF_TEST/ANRF_AISEHack_Code/Ronit/src/utils.py#11-20) | **42** |

### Per-Epoch Flow

1. **Train**: Forward ŌåÆ [objective_loss](file:///home/raj/Documents/CODING/Hackathon/ANRF_TEST/ANRF_AISEHack_Code/Ronit/src/train.py#130-157) ŌåÆ backward with AMP scaling ŌåÆ `unscale_` ŌåÆ `clip_grad_norm_(1.0)` ŌåÆ step ŌåÆ scheduler step
2. **Validate**: Forward ŌåÆ compute [rmse_loss](file:///home/raj/Documents/CODING/Hackathon/ANRF_TEST/ANRF_AISEHack_Code/Ronit/src/train.py#31-44) (metric), [objective_loss](file:///home/raj/Documents/CODING/Hackathon/ANRF_TEST/ANRF_AISEHack_Code/Ronit/src/train.py#130-157), and [persistence_rmse_from_batch](file:///home/raj/Documents/CODING/Hackathon/ANRF_TEST/ANRF_AISEHack_Code/Ronit/src/train.py#203-208)
3. **Checkpoint selection metric**:
   - Mode: `mixed`
   - Formula: `0.7 ├Ś val_objective + 0.3 ├Ś val_rmse`
4. **Persistence gate check**: Every 5 epochs, compare val RMSE to `0.0208` (normalized) / `30.83` ┬Ąg/m┬│

### Persistence Baseline Gate

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Normalized RMSE (t+16 avg) | **0.0208** |
| Physical RMSE | **30.83 ┬Ąg/m┬│** |

The model must beat this persistence baseline (predicting last observed value forward) to be considered useful.

### Early Stopping

- Tracks `selection_metric = 0.7 ├Ś val_objective + 0.3 ├Ś val_rmse`
- Saves best checkpoint to `best_model.pt`
- Stops if no improvement for **8 consecutive epochs**

---

## 10. Inference

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| `batch_size_test` | **16** |
| `test_samples` | **996** |
| `use_tta` | `true` |
| [tta_modes](file:///home/raj/Documents/CODING/Hackathon/ANRF_TEST/ANRF_AISEHack_Code/Ronit/src/inference.py#20-28) | `identity`, `hflip`, `vflip`, `hvflip` |

### Inference Pipeline

1. Load best checkpoint (`best_model.pt`)
2. Build test input: normalize all features, pad cpm25 `[10:26)` with zeros, shape [(996, 8, 26, 140, 124)](file:///home/raj/Documents/CODING/Hackathon/ANRF_TEST/ANRF_AISEHack_Code/Ronit/src/model.py#84-93)
3. **Test-Time Augmentation (TTA)**: For each batch, run 4 augmented passes (identity + 3 flips), average predictions
4. **Denormalize** predictions back to physical ┬Ąg/m┬│
5. Save `preds.npy` of shape [(996, 140, 124, 16)](file:///home/raj/Documents/CODING/Hackathon/ANRF_TEST/ANRF_AISEHack_Code/Ronit/src/model.py#84-93)
6. Assertions: shape = [(996, 140, 124, 16)](file:///home/raj/Documents/CODING/Hackathon/ANRF_TEST/ANRF_AISEHack_Code/Ronit/src/model.py#84-93), all values finite

### Output

| File | Shape | Units |
|------|-------|-------|
| `preds.npy` | [(996, 140, 124, 16)](file:///home/raj/Documents/CODING/Hackathon/ANRF_TEST/ANRF_AISEHack_Code/Ronit/src/model.py#84-93) | Physical PM2.5 ┬Ąg/m┬│ |

